"Among the People" Vol. 67 Published
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House brought out the collection of reminiscences "Among the People" Vol. 67.
 Carried in the book are 19 items of reminiscences illustrating immortal revolutionary exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung for the country and the people and his noble popular traits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reminiscences "The Biggest Wish of the Leader" recount that  the President earnestly told the officials and the people to devote their all to the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, saying it was his biggest wish that they upheld Kim Jong Il  with loyal hearts.
 The reminiscences "Defence of the Country Is Most Ardent Patriotism" give an impressive account of the warm care shown by the President for a woman soldier standing guard at the post of national defence in the uniform of the revolutionary army as her father did and the reminiscences "Immortal Traces in Kalsan" recount the traces of leadership left by him for strengthening the civilian defence forces.
 Included in the reminiscences are "'Holidays' of the Leader" and "Grand Nature-Remaking Project Initiated at the Age of 70" which cites historical facts that the President devoted even his holidays to the prosperity of the country and the happiness of the people in the days of building a new country and energetically guided grand nature-remaking. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The reminiscences "Even in a Souvenir" deals with the President's noble love for the country manifested in his efforts to widely publicize the brilliant culture and history of the Korean nation, while the reminiscences "Paternal Love Reaches the Foot of Mt. Paektu", "If It Is for the People" and "Legend of Love Recounted in Iap" give emotional accounts of the immortal history of leadership of the President for the improvement of the standard of people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reminiscences "Teaching Farming Method", "Traces of Leadership in Ryongchon-ri" and "Scientific Farming Method Taught by the President" say the President visited farms on his way of on-site guidance to learn how crops were doing and teach officials scientific farming method, thus guiding them to strictly apply the Juche-oriented farming method. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also contained in the book are reminiscences recalling the President saw to it that Juche character was established in capital construction and led the officials of a county took care of the people's living in a responsible manner, showed deep concern for the growth of a woman party official, devoted the New Year's Day to bereaved children of fallen revolutionaries with deepest care and heard simple dreams of schoolchildren and wished them a happy future.

Participants in ASFAF Visit Kumsusan Memorial Palace
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Foreign artistes and overseas Korean artistes participating in the 24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival (ASFAF) Wednesday visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung.
 They made bows to the President who lies in state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they looked round the orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles the President received at home and from foreign countries, the mourning hall and a train coach and a car he used for on-the-spot guidance and trips to foreign countries and in the last period of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They made entries in the visitor's book.

Sports Contests for "Mangyongdae Cup" Open
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Sports Contests for "Mangyongdae Cup" opened on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 These contests are a big sports festival that draws sports groups in Pyongyang and local areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their participants will compete in at least 30 events such as football, basketball, volleyball, boxing, judo, swimming and shooting to be held in Pyongyang, Sariwon, Wonsan, Hamhung and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the opening ceremony which took place at the Basketball Gymnasium in Chongchun Street Wednesday were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central�@Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials concerned and sports persons. 
 Mun Jae Dok, chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, in his opening address called on all sports persons to give good accounts of themselves in the matches by fully displaying sports technique they have cultivated in their day-to-day trainings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The opening ceremony was followed by a men's basketball match between the sports group of Kim Il Sung University and the Amnokgang Sports Group.

Kim Yong Nam Calls on Great King of Cambodia at State Guesthouse
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, called on Great King of Cambodia Norodom Sihanouk at a state guesthouse on Wednesday.
 He was accompanied by Minister of Culture Kim Jin Song, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were greeted at the state guesthouse by the Great King, the Great Queen, Cambodian Ambassador to the DPRK Chhorn Hay and other Cambodians.
 At a cordial and friendly conversation Kim Yong Nam warmly congratulated the Great King and the Great Queen on their 54th wedding anniversary and the New Year's Day of Cambodia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam wished the Great King would spend pleasant and joyful days during his stay. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Great King extended profound thanks to supreme leader Kim Jong Il for having shown deep care for him and his wife so that they might spend happy days without any inconvenience since their coming to Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sihanouk also said that they always remember and are grateful that President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il extended disinterested support and solidarity to the Cambodian people during the hardest period of the national liberation struggle in Cambodia. 
 He added that during his visit he witnessed the great achievements made by the Korean people in socialist construction of Juche under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He wished Kim Jong Il good health.
 Kim Yong Nam hosted a luncheon in honor of the Great King.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Air Force Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 12 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, inspected Unit 814 of the Air Force of the KPA.
 Conducted by the commander of the unit, he went round the monument to the on-the-spot guidance of President Kim Il Sung and a room dedicated to the history of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing the historic relics and mementoes associated with the footprints of Kim Il Sung, he said that the undying revolutionary feats performed by Kim Il Sung in building the nation's air force will brilliantly shine with the history of the matchless air force of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He acquainted himself with the unit's performance of duty before watching pilots and technical personnel in training at a technical lecture hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the feats of the unit, greatly satisfied to learn that it has fully prepared all the pilots as self-blasting airmen through a dynamic drive to thoroughly implement the military line of the WPK. He set forth tasks to be carried out by the unit to increase its combat capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He inspected the hero squadron to learn about the ideological education conducted by it and its combat preparedness. Pleased to know that the pilots always remain on the high alert and are fully ready to beat back any enemy's attack, he praised them for reliably standing guard over the sky over the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the admirable airmen are strong in faith and ideology as their hearts are burning with the patriotic resolution to devote their youth and lives to defending the country, he said, adding that such ranks of loyalists are reliably defending the blue sky over the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Then he went round the army-people power station newly built by servicepersons.
 He was briefed on the power station before going round its exterior and interior including the generator room and the electricity distribution room to acquaint himself in detail with its construction and the production of electricity there.
  The technical and equipment management of the power station should be improved to boost the production of quality electricity, he said, advancing the tasks to do so.
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong, Vice Department Director of the WPK Central Committee Hwang Pyong So and Col. General O Kum Chol, commander of the Air Force of the KPA.
